Vice President Kamala Harris visited the Northeast Bronx YMCA in New York to acknowledge the great work happening in communities and highlight the importance of the Build Back Better approach in addressing the needs of families and community members. She emphasized the opportunity Congress has to fix longstanding problems through the Build Back Better Agenda and expressed confidence in reaching a deal, despite the frustrations and tensions involved in the negotiation process. In response to questions about the border, Harris acknowledged the challenges inherited by the administration and the need to reconstruct and improve the immigration system while addressing the root causes of migration. She stated that she currently has no plans to visit the border before the end of the year.